AC   P32837;
GABA-specific permease (GABA-specific transport protein).
"Cloning and expression of the UGA4 gene coding for the inducible
GABA-specific transport protein of Saccharomyces cerevisiae.";
"The nucleotide sequence of Saccharomyces cerevisiae chromosome IV.";
"Uptake of GABA and putrescine by UGA4 on the vacuolar membrane in
Saccharomyces cerevisiae.";
"A global topology map of the Saccharomyces cerevisiae membrane
proteome.";
-!- FUNCTION: Required for high-affinity, high-specificity GABA
    transport. Also transports putrescine.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Vacuole; vacuolar membrane; multi-pass
    membrane protein.
-!- INDUCTION: In the presence of GABA.
-!- MISCELLANEOUS: It requires NPR (nitrogen permease reactivator
    protein) for its full activity.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the amino acid-polyamine-organocation (APC)
    superfamily. Amino acid/choline transporter (ACT) (TC 2.A.3.4)
    family.
